<subSubSection id="4DC4B8C7C98B8CD1772F868577B3881F" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="16CA19C6BEF546EE9397C9B8B59C25B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1AB5DC6D70CBD91CEA38CCC40D7C1AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
The new genus superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName id="94C318AD75FB53EC4D9BAF6DB0895570" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carterocephalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carterocephalus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="65B5C6E5DA17CF25AC4254FAEF5D5FD3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Carterocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lederer, 1852, although it is distinguishable from the latter with regards to the following characters: hindwing undersides with silver spots, a deeply bifurcated V-shaped uncus, juxta a heart-shaped ring, and valvae asymmetrical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A998B0467F882CA3644D904BA434DCC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
The new genus contains only the type species 
<taxonomicName id="61C43727857EAFA91D6D2DE9C7AF1156" authority="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba, 2021" authorityName="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pulchroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pulchroptera pulchra" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="FE2E07793DDE1658D145183EEF948EA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Pulchroptera pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Leech, 1891) comb. nov., with the nominotypical subspecies and a further subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="693AA760B19FE91993A0D08027B5A578" authority="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba, 2021" authorityName="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pulchroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pulchroptera pulchra subsp. ops" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pulchra" subSpecies="ops">
<emphasis id="BA9AB43BF480E931DA4C4740CE5D7437" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Pulchroptera pulchra ops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="844FBAD85050D64A5FD03C44A3E940D6" originalValue="Grum-Grshimaïlo">Grum-Grshimailo</normalizedToken>
, 1891) comb. nov. According to the description of 
<bibRefCitation id="A093CB6DB6B0B404C11BD4DAFF684FC9" author="Evans, WH" journalOrPublisher="British Museum (Natural History), London" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/48223970" refId="B6" refString="Evans, WH, 1949. A Catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia &amp; Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). British Museum (Natural History). London, 502 pp. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/48223970" title="A Catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia &amp; Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). British Museum (Natural History). London, 502 pp." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/48223970" year="1949">Evans (1949)</bibRefCitation>
, in 
<taxonomicName id="7FFF8710EEACA20AA474FEBECD0FE42E" authority="pulchra" authorityName="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pulchroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pulchroptera pulchra subsp. pulchra" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pulchra" subSpecies="pulchra">
<emphasis id="B55CC5C20F52A55FCF1AAFB003616B3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Pulchroptera pulchra pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. the upper side of the hindwing has a cell spot and the submarginal markings are notably more conspicuous, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="C1D9844FD4DEA50434D2ECD87312753C" authority="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba, 2021" authorityName="Hou, Fan &amp; Chiba" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pulchroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pulchroptera pulchra subsp. ops" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pulchra" subSpecies="ops">
<emphasis id="99D67A55126BB58D8689599C624CDD46" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Pulchroptera pulchra ops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. the upper side of the hindwing lacks a cell spot and has conspicuous submarginal markings. Whether the subspecies status of the latter is valid is subject to further verification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4A8E0E57724A1465C14383134132C615" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F542ACF4496C2CDB6592A99AD00238DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F6453C90E40E833F098B4DA58E36F69" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
The name of the genus is taken from the specific epithet of the type species 
<normalizedToken id="25BAF80814A0212A202BA4870E016D15" originalValue="‘pulchr-’">'pulchr-'</normalizedToken>
, meaning beautiful, and 
<normalizedToken id="07BAEF64DD09B3915015CFB25FF64EA7" originalValue="‘optera’">'optera'</normalizedToken>
, meaning wing. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
